
/*
 * 1. The [.text] node is assigned the value "Test".
 * 2. The [strings.length] slot calculates the length of the string found at the node referenced by the expression `:x:@.text`.
 * 3. The result will be an integer representing the character count of the value in [.text], which is 4.
 * 
 * Use cases:
 * - To validate if a string input meets a minimum or maximum length requirement.
 * - For determining the size of a user-provided string before saving to a database.
 * - Useful in generating dynamic summaries or previews based on the length of text fields.
 * - Can assist in string manipulation tasks where substring extraction depends on knowing the original length.
 */
.text:Test
strings.length:x:@.text
